cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AR, cs.SY

The paper proposes a method for making deep learning more resource-efficient, which is a topic that is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The use of neural networks suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), while the focus on efficiency suggests that it could also belong to cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). The use of benchmark datasets and evaluation of energy efficiency suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AR, and cs.SY, in that order.
